The paper deals with monitoring distributed data sources, which is a common problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus is on network monitoring applications (cs.NI) and detecting distributed denial-of-service attacks (cs.CR). The paper also discusses implementing the AMS sampling method in the distributed monitoring model, which could fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) or systems and control (cs.SI).
